# Core Systems / Bridge — Technical Doc

## Overview
Four scripts that form the backbone of the game loop. None are placed in the scene yet — still pending hookup. All are written and ready.

## GameManager.cs
Singleton, DontDestroyOnLoad. Owns all global state.

**Key fields:**
- `totalTime` — 180s (3 minutes)
- `maxHP` — 5
- `maxScore` — 10000
- `timeRemaining`, `currentHP`, `gameActive` — runtime state
- `citySceneName`, `gameOverSceneName` — must match Build Profiles exactly

**Score formula:**
```
MAX_SCORE × (hp/maxHP) × (0.5 + 0.5 × timeRemaining/totalTime)
```
- Full HP + instant finish → approaches 10000
- Full HP + timer expired → 5000
- HP = 0 → 0 (game over)
- Time only contributes 50% weight, so surviving matters more than speed

**Key methods:**
- `StartGame()` — call from main menu Play button
- `TakeDamage(int amount)` — called by CrisisMarker on fail
- `EndGame(GameEndReason)` — internal, fires on HP=0 or timer expiry

**On game end:** saves `FinalScore`, `FinalHP`, `WasPerfect`, `TimeLeft` to PlayerPrefs for GameOver scene to read.

**Events:**
- `OnHPChanged(int current, int max)` — CityHUD subscribes to this
- `OnGameEnded(GameEndReason)` — reason is either `TimerExpired` or `CityDestroyed`

