## CrisisSpawner.cs
Manages spawning CrisisMarkers across the city.

**Key fields:**
- `crisisMarkerPrefab` — the marker prefab
- `spawnPoints` — empty GameObjects placed at valid crisis locations on city map
- `initialSpawnInterval` / `finalSpawnInterval` — ramps from 20s down to 8s over game duration
- `maxActiveCrises` — default 4
- `crisisTypes` — list of `CrisisType` entries, one per minigame

**CrisisType fields:**
- `minigameSceneName` — must exactly match scene name in Build Profiles
- `displayName` — shown on popup
- `mapIcon` — sprite shown on city map
- `timeLimit` — seconds before auto-fail
- `hpDamageOnFail` — default 1

**Spawn logic:**
- Waits for `gameActive = true` before starting
- Picks random unoccupied spawn point
- Picks random CrisisType (uniform random, weighted random noted as future improvement)
- Tracks occupied spawn indices, clears them when marker is resolved or destroyed

